                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“And take the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God;”
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:17 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“But He answered and said, “<b>It is written</b>, ‘Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds from the mouth of God.”
                                                                            <b>Matthew 4:4 NKJV</b> “Jesus said to him, “<b>It is written again</b>, ‘You shall not tempt the LORD your God.’ ””
                                                                            <b>Matthew 4:7 NKJV</b>
                                                                            “Then Jesus said to him, “Away with you, Satan! For it is written, ‘You shall worship the LORD your God, and Him only you shall serve.’ ””
                                                                            <b>Matthew 4:10 NKJV</b>

                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“For the word of God is living and powerful, and sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing even to the division of soul and spirit, and of joints and marrow, and is a discerner of the thoughts and intents of the heart.”
                                                                            <b>Hebrews 4:12 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“For as the rain comes down, and the snow from heaven, And do not return there, But water the earth, And make it bring forth and bud, That it may give seed to the sower And bread to the eater, So shall My word be that goes forth from My mouth; It shall not return to Me void, But it shall accomplish what I please, And it shall prosper in the thing for which I sent it.”
                                                                            <b>Isaiah 55:10-11 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Take up the helmet of salvation and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Jesus wielded the sword of the Spirt in <b>Matthew 4:3-10</b> as He was being tempted by Satan in the wilderness.  Satan challenged Him in the same sense as he did Eve in the garden.  By saying “command these stones to become bread.”  Trying to put doubt in His mind that God wouldn’t provide.  Jesus immediately used the Sword “It is written, Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds from the mouth of God.” In verse 6 Satan challenges Jesus to jump over the cliff.  Jesus again uses the Sword, “ It is written again, You shall not tempt the LORD your God.”  In verse 8 Satan showed Jesus all the kingdoms of the world and all their glory saying they could all be Yours requesting Jesus bow down and worship him.  Again the Sword.  “Away with you, Satan. It is written, You shall worship the LORD your God, and Him only you shall serve.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">In each scenario Jesus applied the scripture that addressed the type of attack.  The emphasis is also on <b>“It is written.”</b>  We are as His people blessed to have a life manual complete in all ways.  The direction and answers to all of life situations are written in this one book.  It is a treasure to be cherished, read and applied to our lives.
                                                                            <b>Hebrews 4:12</b> tells us it is sharper than any two edged sword.  It divides the soul and  spirit, joints and marrow, and discerns the thoughts and intent of our hearts.
                                                                            The word heals us, cleanses us, counsels us, strengthens us, hides within our hearts...plus so much more.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">A young girl goes to babysit for her mom’s friend...in later years she becomes a youth pastor...the family she babysat for celebrated her achievement, and asked what made you go in this direction.  Her reply was deafening.  She said every time I babysat for you your Bible was in a different place, a different room, on the couch, the floor, the bedroom etc..
                                                                            See how marvelously the word of God can witness to someone.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">One must know the word to employ it as the sword it is.  It is our mighty and the most  powerful weapon against principalities, powers, the rulers of darkness of this age, against spiritual hosts of wickedness in the heavenly places. The word that has come forth from His mouth will not return void, it will accomplish what He pleases it to, and it will prosper for why He sent it.  His promise to use...
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Father Your word is forever settled in heaven, it can and will not ever change.  Your faithfulness has endure through out all generations, and we here in this generation have no reason to doubt Your faithfulness to give us the understanding of Your word.  May we receive Your promise to us that the Holy Spirit will lead us into all truth.  May we take these truths and apply them to live out our lives glorifying You.  I pray for a new hunger within each of us to know Your word that we will be better suited to wield the sword of the Spirit and be the victorious soldier to pierce, penetrate and prevail as we fight the good fight and stay focus on the victory just as they marched around Jericho we would see the walls of darkness fall as Your light is shown through us and we are used for Your service.  In Jesus name...Amen and AMEN!
                                                                        </p>
